BILL AS INTRODUCED H.153
2025 Page 2 of 2
1 An act relating to expanding family access to certified copies of birth and
2 death certificates
3 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
4 Sec. 1. 18 V.S.A. § 5016 is amended to read:
5 § 5016. BIRTH AND DEATH CERTIFICATES; COPIES; INSPECTION
6 * * *
7 (b) Certified copies.
8 * * *
9 (2) Only the following persons shall be eligible for a certified copy of a
10 birth or death certificate:
11 (A) the registrant or his or her the registrant’s spouse, child,
12 grandchild, parent, sibling, grandparent, aunt, uncle, nephew, niece, or
13 guardian; a person petitioning to open a decedent’s estate; a court-appointed
14 executor or administrator; or the legal representative of any of these;
15 * * *
16 Sec. 2. EFFECTIVE DATE
17 This act shall take effect on July 1, 2025.
